  "title" : "A for-loop to iterate over an enum in Java",
  "body" : "<p>I have an <code>enum</code> in Java for the cardinal and intermediate directions:</p>\n<pre><code>public enum Direction {\n   NORTH,\n   NORTHEAST,\n   EAST,\n   SOUTHEAST,\n   SOUTH,\n   SOUTHWEST,\n   WEST,\n   NORTHWEST\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>How can I write a <code>for</code> loop that iterates through each of these <code>enum</code> values?</p>\n"
